flowchart_nodes.name: ReActAgent
flowchart_nodes.purpose:
What is a ReAct Agent? An AI agent that interleaves reasoning (thinking) and acting, using observations from the environment to guide its next step.

Why is it used? To reduce errors from pure reasoning and improve decisions by grounding thoughts in real-time feedback.

When does it matter? In complex, multi-step tasks where decisions depend on intermediate results (e.g., tool use, web search, planning).

What did it influence? Modern agentic AI design, tool-using LLMs, and frameworks that combine reasoning with actions in real-world environments.

flowchart_nodes.name: ShalloAgent
flowchart_nodes.purpose:
What is a Shallow Agent? An agent that makes decisions using simple rules or heuristics without deep reasoning or long-term planning.

Why is it used? Because it is fast, inexpensive, and sufficient for simple, well-defined problems.

When does it matter? When tasks are predictable, time-critical, or do not require complex reasoning.

What did it influence? Early artificial intelligence systems, rule-based expert systems, and basic automation tools.

flowchart_nodes.name: Agent
flowchart_nodes.purpose:
What is an Agent? An entity that perceives its environment, makes decisions, and takes actions to achieve a goal.

Why is it used? To automate goal-oriented behavior without constant human control.

When does it matter? When systems must adapt, decide, or act autonomously in changing environments.

What did it influence? Artificial intelligence, robotics, autonomous systems, and modern AI agents (chatbots, planners, tool-using models)

flowchart_nodes.name: DeepAgent
flowchart_nodes.purpose:
What is a Deep Agent? An agent that uses deep learning models to reason, learn representations, and make decisions from complex data.

Why is it used? To handle high-dimensional, unstructured inputs (text, images, speech) and learn from experience.

When does it matter? In complex, uncertain environments requiring learning, generalization, and long-term decision-making.

What did it influence? Modern AI systems such as deep reinforcement learning, autonomous driving, game-playing AIs, and large language model agents.
